4 hours ago, xHOGUEx said:

mono.dll caused an Access Violation (0xc0000005)
  in module mono.dll at 0033:9f421504.

Read from location 00000000 caused an access violation.

Looks pretty much like the usual case of old mods. When you uninstall the game Steam will not remove files that either the game created or you put there yourself. So go to your GameData folder and delete anything that is not the Squad folder and the SquadExpansion folder if you bought the DLC. If you ever edited something inside the Squad folder you might want to completely delete the whole Kerbal Space Program folder and reinstall the game.

If that's not helping people will probably need the output log that you can find here: https://docs.unity3d.com/Manual/LogFiles.html

Turned out, after trying to failure to delete old files and work stopping me for days, I had to re-download the History Expansion and it fully loaded. Thanks for the help and can't wait to make a lot of explosions.
